# Deny-by-default: ignore everything, then allow specific files below.
*

# Allow descending into subdirectories (required before allowing files).
!*/

# Julia source & package metadata
!*.jl
!*.toml
!*.cff

# Extensions files for Julia packages
!ext/
!ext/*.jl

# Docs & repo metadata. Named one by one rather than `!*.md`: a blanket
# allow on markdown lets working notes and scratch files into the tree by
# default, which is the opposite of what deny-by-default is for. A pattern
# with no slash matches at any depth, so `!README.md` covers docs/README.md
# too. Add a line here when a document is meant to be published.
!README.md
!CHANGELOG.md
!ROADMAP.md
!CONTRIBUTING.md
!CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
!SECURITY.md
!LICENSE
!LICENSE.*
!CITATION*
!.gitignore
!.gitattributes
!.editorconfig

# Tooling configs
!*.yml
!*.yaml
!*.json
!*.sh
!Makefile

# Re-ignore Julia / docs build artifacts (overrides allow list above).
Manifest.toml
/docs/build/
/docs/site/
*.jl.cov
*.jl.*.cov
*.jl.mem
lcov.info

# Renders are outputs and regenerate themselves. The version-controlled
# wallpapers live in the config repo, not here.
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.heic
*.mp4
*.webm

# Re-ignore editor / OS / env files.
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
.env
.env.local
